  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619454855260-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619454855260-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619454855260-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619454855260-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619454855260-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomatoes </strong>into wedges</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1606747743810-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1606747743810-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1606747743810-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1606747743810-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1606747743810-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> to the dish with your<strong> dried oregano</strong>, <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>baharat</strong> and cook for 1-2 min, breaking the mince into rough, large chunks until very lightly browned all over</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1606747748522-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1606747748522-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1606747748522-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1606747748522-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1606747748522-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and slice into rings</p><p>Add the <strong>pepper rings</strong> and<strong> tomato wedges </strong>to the dish, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good stir</p><p>Put the dish in the oven, uncovered, for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1606747753194-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1606747753194-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1606747753194-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1606747753194-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-1606747753194-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 250ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml] </span>[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and set aside for later – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1606747757395-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1606747757395-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1606747757395-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1606747757395-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-1606747757395-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 15 min, remove the dish from the oven and stir through your <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> and <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and return the dish to the oven for 15 min further until the lamb is cooked (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Turkish-style lamb bulgur pilaf</strong></p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves </strong>from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1606747763756-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1606747763756-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1606747763756-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1606747763756-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1606747763756-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 15 min, remove the dish from the oven and leave to stand (keep the lid on!) for 10 min further</p><p>Tip: This will help to make the bulgur fluffy!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1606747767963-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1606747767963-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1606747767963-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1606747767963-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-1606747767963-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, fluff the <strong>Turkish-style lamb bulgur pilaf </strong>with a fork</p><p>Dollop your<strong> natural yoghurt </strong>over the top and scatter the<strong> chopped mint </strong>all over</p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>sumac</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
